Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[instrumental theme music playing]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.99,0:01:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Maureen] There are eclipsing binaries,\Nastrometric binaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.78,0:01:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,spectroscopic binaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.25,0:01:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to tell which one we're in\Nwithout a map of the star system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.34,0:01:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-[John] You're doing it again.\N-[Maureen] Doing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.67,0:01:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.09,0:01:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Using astrophysics\Nas a smokescreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.26,0:01:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell me the bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.39,0:01:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[Maureen] Okay, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.02,0:01:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is our planet and this is a sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.44,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a typical orbit looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I'm guessing\Nour orbit isn't typical.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.12,0:02:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[Maureen] The way the ecosphere\Nhas been behaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.91,0:02:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the longer days\Nand the increased temperatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.29,0:02:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't figure it out\Nuntil I got up there and I saw this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A coffee mug?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A black hole.\NHiding just off the shoulder of our sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.93,0:02:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The gravitational pull\Nis altering the orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.06,0:02:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,pulling our planet closer and closer,\Nuntil, when it makes this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.48,0:02:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing on the surface,\NI mean nothing, will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How long do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.20,0:02:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Till the planet becomes uninhabitable?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Weeks, maybe months.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.62,0:02:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to know\Nwithout more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.09,0:02:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a decision to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:02:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we tell people?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] You're asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[Maureen] Yeah, I'm asking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.14,0:03:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Honestly, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.81,0:03:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, God, Maureen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you should have seen their faces\Nout there tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking to me to answer questions\Nabout that machine that I don't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, tomorrow I get to clean up that mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-This one--\N-It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you decide, I'll support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] \NTwenty-seven people died crashing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands, wives, friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead because of what that thing did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What about last night?\NIt was protecting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-It was defending itself!\N-Who knows what would've happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.75,0:04:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-Maybe it can help us--\N-Please! Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.08,0:04:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One at a time.\NLet's not have this devolve into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.46,0:04:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor, if I could make a suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should hear from someone\Nwho has seen, firsthand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.30,0:04:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what this thing is capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Angela, would you like\Nto tell us anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.11,0:04:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was the seventh musician\Nchosen for relocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.99,0:04:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He played cello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.16,0:04:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved football and hated the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[voice breaking]\NHe was the best part of my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that thing murdered him\Nin front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be forced to sit here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,listening to people wonder\Nhow they can use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.48,0:05:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sickens me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the best course of action would be\Nto treat this as we would at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If a man had committed\Nany of these crimes--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.82,0:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.28,0:05:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.45,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Angela...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.37,0:05:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry\Nabout what happened to your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing that we can do or say\Nthat can replace that loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think that it's important\Nthat we understand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that the robot has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.64,0:05:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-Changed? John, what are you--\N-Let him speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.72,0:05:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Think of it like a computer\Nthat's been rebooted or reprogrammed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.15,0:06:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't know\Nwhat the hell this thing was before,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.11,0:06:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or why it's here now,\Nbut what I do know is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.70,0:06:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that the only reason\Nmy daughter is alive today
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is because that machine saved her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it kept my family safe...\Nwhen I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in a place where I think\Nwe'd all like to feel a little safer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.67,0:06:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs] Yeah, and, uh...\Nwhat if it changes again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.64,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's going to keep us safe from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it for yourself.\NIt listens to my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd put our safety\Nin the hands of a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.44,0:06:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Only difference is,\Nnow you all know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, everyone. I think we should try\Nand reach a consensus here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.57,0:06:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] Let's begin with the fact\Nthat we can't control this thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.20,0:06:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-nor do we understand it.\N-[man 2] We might need its help again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[chatter continues indistinctly]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Angela panting]\N-Angela, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.21,0:07:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to say, you're not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.30,0:07:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[stammers]\NI lost a very dear friend in the crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I buried her with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Very sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.18,0:07:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to see that you're on your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you were a fighter\Nwhen we found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you found me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.78,0:07:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Don West didn't mention\Nthat I was there with...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.28,0:07:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the one who insisted that... [sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.37,0:07:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.\NSome people need to feel like a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.13,0:07:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just happy to see you're on the mend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.71,0:07:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For what it's worth,\Nafter trauma like you've endured,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be helpful\Nto speak with a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.27,0:08:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a therapist.\NI'd be happy to help you--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[stutters] No, I appreciate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.15,0:08:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm focusing on my physical therapy\Nat the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.48,0:08:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.69,0:08:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.82,0:08:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy your walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.37,0:08:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[indistinct chatter]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Souvenir?\N-Ah, research.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.35,0:08:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I brought some of that back, too,\Nwould that be worth something to somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... only if you could keep it\Nfrom becoming contaminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you teach me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.57,0:08:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[Naoko chuckles and speaks Japanese]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.36,0:08:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[continues speaking Japanese]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:08:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Hiroki sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-[in English] Not enough time.\N-Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.04,0:09:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[speaking Japanese]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.88,0:09:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[in English] Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.05,0:09:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Oh, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.30,0:09:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunts] What's this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.76,0:09:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Protection. In case you didn't notice,\Nit's getting dangerous around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.10,0:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time a pretty lady\Noffered me protection,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.81,0:09:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-it was because we were--\N-[footsteps thudding]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.71,0:09:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you should go back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought we could help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.01,0:09:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there are a lot of heavy things\Nand he can--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:10:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside. Just until your dad gets back.\NGo on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.22,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.39,0:10:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[footsteps receding]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.15,0:10:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.62,0:10:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[Penny] Having fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.37,0:10:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... [sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.87,0:10:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're wondering if rotting meat\Nsmells the same here as it does on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then the answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.54,0:10:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm going swimming at the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.84,0:10:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-We haven't tested the water yet.\N-So?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.97,0:10:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So it could kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.01,0:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I told my dad I'd do this, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.43,0:10:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, whatever. I'm gonna go.\NYou can come if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.69,0:10:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[stutters]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[vehicle approaching]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:10:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[Vijay panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.03,0:11:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,John, tell Maureen I'd like to talk to her\Nwhen she has a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.70,0:11:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.50,0:11:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're out of fuel, can't reach\Nthe Resolute, audibly or visibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Might be time to consider the reality\Nof long-term habitation of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.71,0:11:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'll let her know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.23,0:11:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Maureen] How'd it go?\N-What'd they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.06,0:11:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-The robot stays.\N-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.07,0:11:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep it away from other people,\Nyou report any changes in behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.03,0:11:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and register its whereabouts at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no problem.\NI want to show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.58,0:11:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.29,0:11:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-He doesn't get it.\N-Let him be happy for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.80,0:12:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-Victor's outside. Wants to talk.\N-[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.51,0:12:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You gonna tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.14,0:12:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The coffee mug.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.10,0:12:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a list.\NStuff the robot could do to help people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when they see how awesome he is,\Nthey'll accept him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I had something else in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.65,0:12:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why don't you help me today?\N-With what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you later.\NIt's kind of a father-son thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.54,0:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[footsteps approaching]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I forgot,\Nit's more of a father-son-robot thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.14,0:12:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,John, are you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.35,0:12:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Right. We're heading off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, those Robinsons\Ncan be a real pain in the ass, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.45,0:13:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Always sticking their noses in--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.99,0:13:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-Sorry, do I know you?\N-Don West.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.78,0:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't expect a guy like you\Nto know a guy like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.99,0:13:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but you look like someone\Nwho can get things done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.08,0:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to Peter Beckert.\NHe handles my affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.71,0:13:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I told you\NI knew where a man could get rocket fuel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, enough to get everyone here\Noff this planet, back into space?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say you were mistaken. Whatever fuel \Nwas left in the Jupiters is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.26,0:13:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the eels. Yeah.\NYeah, heard about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. [chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.68,0:13:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,From what I understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those slippery bastards\Nneed moisture to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.94,0:13:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My crew and I, we crashed in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.77,0:13:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Auxiliary fuel tanks, untouched,\Njust sitting there,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.44,0:13:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for a smart community leader\Nto claim them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.74,0:13:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dare I say, that man will be a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.24,0:13:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would that make you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Significantly wealthier.\NYou can arrange that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,[both speaking indistinctly]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.38,0:14:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don] Great. See you in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.09,0:14:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-[grunts softly]\N-What were you two talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your schedule like\Nthe next 24 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.27,0:14:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.30,0:14:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.74,0:15:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[Maureen grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.32,0:15:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.32,0:15:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just bringing some supplies\Nin case we have to spend--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.12,0:15:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think you're going, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:15:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.04,0:16:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to rest. You haven't\Ngiven yourself time to properly heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.96,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm healing fine. I'll heal later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.50,0:16:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you fully comprehend\Nhow badly we need that fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.22,0:16:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I fully do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why we can't bring anyone\Nwhose physical limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,might get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.35,0:16:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a straightforward thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.06,0:16:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We find the Jupiter, we transfer the fuel,\Nwe bring it home. We got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.69,0:16:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let someone else save the day for once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-[chuckles] It's not that, it's-- [sighs]\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.99,0:16:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.53,0:16:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make sure\Nyou bring that fuel back safely, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be safe out there.\NYou don't know what you might find.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.88,0:16:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.23,0:17:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs deeply]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-Reading anything interesting?\N-[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.87,0:17:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish. [chuckles softly] Just work stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.71,0:17:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.63,0:17:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Have many people been talking to you?\NIn a professional capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, some. It's an unusual time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.59,0:17:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. [chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to talk to me?\NIn a professional capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.43,0:17:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,-I wouldn't want to impose.\N-Not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever spoken\Nto a therapist before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.24,0:17:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No. [chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:17:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You and John--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, that wouldn't have worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Never know until you try.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.12,0:18:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles] Yeah, well,\Nit's a bit late for that anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.63,0:18:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.54,0:18:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about you, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.97,0:18:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering how you deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.30,0:18:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Being the keeper of all those secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.85,0:18:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,With all the things people tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.06,0:18:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.77,0:18:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's just... part of the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.53,0:18:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you ever feel a responsibility to...\NI don't know, tell someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't. Doctor-patient privilege.\N[chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.21,0:18:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you found something out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.54,0:18:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that really would impact\Nsomeone else's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how do you keep that in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.42,0:18:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, here's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.97,0:19:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to find a place inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.85,0:19:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a little box...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,where you put things\Nyou don't want anyone else to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that box has to be airtight,\Nso nothing gets out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.08,0:19:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Once something goes in there,\Nit stays in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where it can't hurt you... or anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.59,0:19:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only way to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.26,0:19:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-Okay.\N-Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.10,0:19:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something that you'd like me\Nto help put in your box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.23,0:19:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[device beeping]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Smith speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.07,0:20:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela] It's Angela. We spoke earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.03,0:20:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.07,0:20:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If the offer still stands, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, it's a patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.66,0:20:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, yes. Oh, of course, yeah.\N-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.17,0:20:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll talk again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.79,0:20:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.59,0:20:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Angela. Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.59,0:20:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at the Watanabe Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.68,0:20:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.81,0:20:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Come on, Will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay, but, uh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.48,0:20:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have ones like that back on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.71,0:20:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.35,0:21:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.39,0:21:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.10,0:21:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.28,0:21:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You teach him to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.66,0:21:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will] No. I guess he must've seen\None of us doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.54,0:21:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess he's, uh... I guess he's learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.04,0:21:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.71,0:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey, Dad?\N-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.71,0:21:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I just realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-I forgot to say thank you.\N-For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sticking up for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sticking up for anybody.\NI was just stating the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.60,0:21:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But still.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.98,0:21:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine what it's gonna be like\Nwhen we get to Alpha Centauri?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.94,0:22:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be the only kid with his own robot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not get ahead of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.15,0:22:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Penny's always saying\Nhow she wants to write a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.65,0:22:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-Maybe she can write it about us.\N-Will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.78,0:22:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. What are we doing exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.12,0:22:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] You'll find out when we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.89,0:22:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Repaired about a hundred of these,\Nnever once got to drive one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.72,0:22:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But you do know how to drive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.48,0:22:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-[distant explosion]\N-What the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.31,0:22:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[explosions continue]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.74,0:22:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-Must be gas, trapped below the surface.\N-What, like a space fart?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.45,0:22:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They're called cryogeysers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.16,0:22:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On Mars, they spit CO2.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:22:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On Triton, it's nitrogen.\NHeat from the sun--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, whatever.\NIs it safe to keep going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.50,0:23:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we stay up here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.67,0:23:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't drive\Ninto the field of exploding rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.21,0:23:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[Victor over radio]\NWhat's going on? You guys lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.34,0:23:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a negative, Captain.\NWe're just plotting our course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.47,0:23:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not here for sightseeing.\NLet's move.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.64,0:23:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,-[eruption booms continue]\N-[grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.10,0:23:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's the best idea this guy has had.\N-How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.44,0:23:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.31,0:23:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,["Panama" playing over speakers]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.90,0:23:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don, this isn't a road trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.69,0:23:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.70,0:23:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Oh, yeah ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.96,0:23:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.92,0:23:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, this thing can move!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.34,0:23:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Jump back ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.13,0:23:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ What's that sound? ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.22,0:23:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Here she comes\NFull blast and top down ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.39,0:23:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughs]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.72,0:24:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-[man] Whoa, whoa, whoa.\N-You're not supposed to open that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.23,0:24:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they put a sunroof\Nif we couldn't open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.64,0:24:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a sunroof.\NIt's an emergency escape hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.77,0:24:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Given everything that's happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you think\Nwe deserve a little escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.36,0:24:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you wanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.49,0:24:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Doc.\NGet up there, reach up to the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.37,0:24:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Give us a "whoo-hoo"\Nlike it's a limo on prom night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.83,0:24:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah, well, I never went to prom.\N-Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.91,0:24:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I was studying for MCATS.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.37,0:24:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you, my nerdy friend,\Nhave a lot of catching up to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.67,0:24:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,-Up you go. Come on.\N-[woman] Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.67,0:24:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come on, Judy.\N-Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.96,0:24:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Don] Come on, Doc.\N-[woman] Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.55,0:24:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[man] Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.80,0:24:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, finally. Loosening up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.89,0:24:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Panama ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.35,0:24:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-♪ Panama, Panama ♪\N-Whoo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.94,0:24:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Panama ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.61,0:24:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.91,0:24:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[Peter] What is she doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.32,0:24:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[woman chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.28,0:25:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like she's having fun. Can we--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.66,0:25:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Diane, we cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.58,0:25:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Get her back inside. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.96,0:25:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back. Come back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.50,0:25:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Copy that, sir.\NWe're having visibility issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.21,0:25:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-We got bug ass all over the windshield.\N-[Victor over radio] Enough, West.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.80,0:25:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Better pray that fuel is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.34,0:25:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing that this is our last chance\Noff this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.39,0:25:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,think we better all pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Panama ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.02,0:25:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Panama ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.48,0:25:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Panama ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.43,0:26:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not much of an advertisement\Nfor space travel, are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.27,0:26:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It should come with a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.27,0:26:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your trip to Alpha Centauri may cause\Nanxiety and high blood pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.65,0:26:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Side effects could include\Nloss of communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.11,0:26:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,eels in your fuel tank."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.15,0:26:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Alien robots."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.91,0:26:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I should have said something.\NEspecially to you, and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.54,0:26:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, understood. Personal choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.08,0:26:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.84,0:26:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something, though,\Nthat I need to share with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.21,0:26:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You have family here, and I...\N[sighs] You deserve to know that--
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.43,0:26:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That they may not be safe here\Nmuch longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.31,0:26:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How... What? How did you--
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.56,0:26:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky guess. But there are signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.98,0:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Erratic weather patterns,\Nwildlife migration.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.27,0:26:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the oldest trees have only one ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.65,0:26:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The life cycle on this planet\Nis quite remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.99,0:27:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Birth, death, repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.07,0:27:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.37,0:27:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have been irresponsible.\NCause panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.83,0:27:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw how they were\Nwith your boy's machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.91,0:27:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're scientists, Maureen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.79,0:27:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because we know something,\Nwe're not compelled to broadcast it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.21,0:27:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Information does not exist in isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.26,0:27:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's consequences. Context.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.26,0:27:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we tell our children?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.68,0:27:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If they come back with the fuel,\Nwe'll all get off this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.85,0:27:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody will be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.48,0:27:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Go dress your wounds, get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.24,0:27:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll need you when they get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.42,0:27:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[Vijay] How far are we going exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.75,0:27:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Have you ever heard\Nof the phrase "carpe diem"?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.46,0:27:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, "seize the day."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.21,0:28:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But can't we seize it\Nfrom the safety of the Jupiter?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.72,0:28:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is your sense of adventure?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.55,0:28:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on an alien planet.\NHow much more adventure do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.60,0:28:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just, like, a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.19,0:28:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you will follow me...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.44,0:28:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-It's a cool waterfall, Penny.\N-Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.37,0:28:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It dried up. It's been getting hotter,\Nmaybe the glacier melted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.70,0:28:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[scoffs] This planet sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.29,0:28:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.21,0:28:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-We could go somewhere else--\N-No, I had it all planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.09,0:28:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All what planned?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.80,0:28:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This. Here. You. Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.43,0:28:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna fall in\Nand pretend to be in trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.97,0:28:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you would jump in and save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.60,0:28:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would be wet and laughing\Nat how stupid it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.43,0:28:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you would lean in and...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.23,0:28:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-And what?\N-Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.90,0:29:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on,\Nit was just getting to the good part.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.61,0:29:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not funny. Forget it, it's ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.11,0:29:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.28,0:29:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-maybe tomorrow we can do something.\N-[Penny] No, we can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.78,0:29:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-We have plenty of time.\N-No, actually, we don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.29,0:29:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're stranded here, Penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.00,0:29:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have all the time we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.29,0:29:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The planet is dying, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.26,0:29:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.67,0:29:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[Penny] I shouldn't have said anything.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.84,0:29:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you... What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.68,0:29:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.89,0:29:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom says that there's\Na giant black hole somewhere up there,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.69,0:29:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I know is that no one\Nand nothing is gonna survive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.78,0:29:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.91,0:29:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to tell people. My dad--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.36,0:29:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No, no, no.\NI'm not even supposed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.79,0:29:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.62,0:29:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, promise me\Nyou're not gonna tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.62,0:29:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-Promise me.\N-Okay, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.30,0:30:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.61,0:30:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.45,0:30:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was here. It was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.01,0:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[Peter] I knew this was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.14,0:30:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.73,0:31:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought us all the way here for\N"Maybe it fell"?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.77,0:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal's off, West. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.07,0:31:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody load up.\NMaybe we'll get back before dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.86,0:31:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he mean, "deal's off"?\NWhat deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.82,0:31:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nothing. It doesn't matter.\N-[Victor] Oh, what, he didn't tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.41,0:31:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your pal here demanded money\Nto show us where the fuel was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.08,0:31:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a real hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.58,0:31:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.50,0:31:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In my defense, it was supposed to be\Na confidential-type arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.97,0:31:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about our survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.22,0:31:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,life and death,\Nand you were holding it hostage?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.93,0:31:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, when a doctor gets paid\Nfor saving someone's life, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.81,0:31:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-But when a guy like me--\N-That's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Different how? If the fuel was here,\Neveryone would've been saved 'cause of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.40,0:31:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You get on a shuttle to the new world.\NWhat do I get?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.90,0:31:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A hearty handshake
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.03,0:31:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and a ticket back to a dying planet\Nwith no future.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.66,0:31:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So forgive me, princess,\Nif I ask for a little compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.37,0:31:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[metallic thud]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.79,0:32:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.88,0:32:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God! It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.09,0:32:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's here!\NCome here, we've been standing on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.76,0:32:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[both grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.22,0:32:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[Judy] Look for the top hatch.\N[panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.89,0:32:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[rumbles]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.89,0:32:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Judy] Whoa, whoa!\N-Okay, whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.60,0:32:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. Slow, slow, slow. Back up slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.61,0:32:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I knew it was here the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.69,0:32:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know if the fuel's still inside.\NDon't count your chickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.86,0:32:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I won't be counting them, sir.\NI only have the one. Her name is Debbie.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.37,0:32:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who's got the shovel?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.46,0:32:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.46,0:32:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.80,0:32:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the meter, tank's full.\NJust like West said.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.39,0:32:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Apology accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.14,0:33:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill her up. Let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.20,0:33:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[panting] This is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.58,0:33:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.00,0:33:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're not here for the view, Will.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.63,0:33:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did we hike up all this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.34,0:33:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab me a rock from over there.\NBig one, bring it over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.43,0:33:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why?\N-Just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.35,0:33:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, I need to go grab a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.52,0:33:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.40,0:33:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.65,0:33:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.91,0:34:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Will grunts]\N-[John] No, no, no, a larger one.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.87,0:34:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Big as you can carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.75,0:34:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.09,0:34:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.97,0:34:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.31,0:34:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.64,0:34:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[continues grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.40,0:34:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.32,0:34:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite. We need 26 more just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.16,0:34:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What? [panting] Am I being punished?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.24,0:34:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.96,0:34:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just trying to help you understand\Nthat you have a responsibility now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.50,0:34:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about him. Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.72,0:35:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.64,0:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I already know what I'm doing, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.31,0:35:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can control him. You saw.\NHe listens to me. He does what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.14,0:35:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Will, he is not a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.98,0:35:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. He's more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.23,0:35:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my friend.\NHe's there when I need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.87,0:35:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But he wasn't always your friend, was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.71,0:35:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[whispers] No.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.71,0:35:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As much as we'd all like\Nto change the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.47,0:35:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,undo our mistakes, we can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.30,0:35:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to live with our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.64,0:35:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in honor of that,\Nwe're gonna place 27 stones here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.27,0:35:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A cairn.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.28,0:36:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A monument to all those\Nwho lost their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.90,0:36:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in the attack on the Resolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.83,0:36:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, today, I...\NI spoke to a woman named Angela.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.26,0:36:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She lost her husband on the Resolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.60,0:36:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This first one's for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.15,0:36:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,[Smith] In order to release the pain,\Nyou have to acknowledge its source.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.78,0:36:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.12,0:36:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.41,0:36:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[Smith] Words are a gateway\Nto your emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.08,0:36:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to start by sharing\Nwhat you remember about that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.63,0:37:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.72,0:37:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when the alarm went off,\Nwe had no idea what it was for.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.30,0:37:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember Josh making jokes\Nso I wouldn't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.27,0:37:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about the moment\Nwhere you first encountered the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.78,0:37:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside the hangar,\Nthere was panic, running, shoving.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.99,0:37:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, we thought \Nit's just the way people are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.62,0:37:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to be the first ones\Nto reach their Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.50,0:37:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, we realized
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.88,0:37:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they weren't running toward something.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.09,0:37:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They were running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That... thing was in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.44,0:38:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who got in its path,\Nit just... eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.28,0:38:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[Smith] You're doing great, Angela.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.70,0:38:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to access\Nyour sense memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.54,0:38:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to lie down...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.92,0:38:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.30,0:38:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to focus on the sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.35,0:38:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the smells.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.89,0:38:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela] There's a strange metallic buzz,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.07,0:38:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like something very close,\Nexcept it's everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.95,0:38:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I smell burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.12,0:39:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[sniffs, voice breaking] People burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.25,0:39:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.55,0:39:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela] Red. Emergency lighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.97,0:39:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was hard to make out where we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.64,0:39:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Josh held my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.85,0:39:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to skirt the perimeter\Nto our Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.31,0:39:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was... It was so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.86,0:39:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.07,0:39:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.70,0:39:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[sniffles] His body went rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.54,0:39:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[sobs]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.21,0:39:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He was hot, searing, white heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.84,0:39:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't let go of his hand. [crying]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.97,0:39:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It had burned into mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.81,0:40:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[crying]
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.31,0:40:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NCan we please not do this anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.32,0:40:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.69,0:40:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we've gone far enough\Nfor this session.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.36,0:40:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought talking about it\Nwould make me feel better,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but I feel worse. [crying]
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.16,0:40:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[stammers] These things, they take time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.04,0:40:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we don't have time?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.13,0:40:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Angela, I... I understand your anger...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.55,0:40:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that this thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.26,0:40:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that did this to your husband\Nis being welcomed among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.85,0:40:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But what prevents people\Nfrom moving on from tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.73,0:40:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is a feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.69,0:40:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's something they could do\Nto change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.40,0:40:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But there isn't. There simply isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.99,0:41:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All we can do is hope, pray...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.62,0:41:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't happen to anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.96,0:41:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there is something I could do?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.26,0:41:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Something more than just hoping\Nand praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.30,0:41:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Angela,\Nbut I'm gonna have to ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.43,0:41:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to refrain from saying anything further\Non this subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.81,0:41:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.10,0:41:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-[sighs] We can pick it up tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.48,0:41:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just make me relive all that\Nand then--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.40,0:41:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We can pick this up tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.99,0:41:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[stutters] You can't just abandon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.49,0:41:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Smith?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.33,0:41:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela sobbing]
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.09,0:41:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-[sighs] Last one.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.09,0:41:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:41:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.39,0:42:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,-[grunts]\N-I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.72,0:42:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.65,0:42:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.78,0:42:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.25,0:42:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunting and panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.34,0:42:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,[continues grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.55,0:42:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[John sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.31,0:42:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs] Let's hope\Nwe never have to add another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.57,0:43:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All clear! [echoing]
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.62,0:43:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we good?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.41,0:43:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-Are you referring to our arrangement?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.66,0:43:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're good\Nwhen we get the fuel safely back.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.75,0:43:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.04,0:43:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you need to stop standing around\Nand start helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.42,0:43:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How much longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.46,0:43:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we start the transfer,\Nabout three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.38,0:43:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, uh, let's try and make it two.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.97,0:43:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to change\Nthe laws of physics, or just lie to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.73,0:43:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, everyone, listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.06,0:43:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In just three hours, we're gonna have\Na tank full of liquid methane
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.23,0:43:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,ready for transport. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.45,0:43:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.82,0:43:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-Me?\N-Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.78,0:43:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I was just wondering\Nwhat we're gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.95,0:43:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Jupiter falls off the edge,\Ntakes the fuel tank with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.16,0:43:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly we're hoping\Nthat's not gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.12,0:43:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you can have all the hope you want,\Nbut gravity may have other plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.34,0:43:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Vic, the west side of the Jupiter\Nis hanging over the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.47,0:44:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the auxiliary fuel supply,\Nthat's on the east side.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.22,0:44:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As we transfer the fuel out,\Nthe east side gets lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.80,0:44:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight shifts to the west side,\Nsending it over the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.64,0:44:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And since our hose\Nis connected to the tanker...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.52,0:44:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so do you have a better idea?\NOr do you want us to pay for that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.61,0:44:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We use the Chariots as an anchor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.44,0:44:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We dig down,\Nattach the towlines to the Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.82,0:44:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With the torque in the engines,\Nwe counteract the shift in the weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.45,0:44:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Don] Hmm.\N-Will that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.87,0:44:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It might. Just gotta get the right guy\Nbehind the wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.00,0:44:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or right girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.91,0:44:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No offense,\Nbut who do you expect to handle this?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.96,0:44:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who saves lives\Nor somebody who gambles with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.71,0:44:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No offense? How is that not offensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.47,0:44:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let us down, Robinson.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.28,0:45:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[Penny]\NI'm sorry I kinda freaked out back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.61,0:45:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.07,0:45:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.91,0:45:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost forgot.\NEveryone knows about the robot,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.79,0:45:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so guess I don't need that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.96,0:45:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.80,0:45:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. Back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.26,0:45:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody does embarrassing things\Nwhen they think they're gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.64,0:45:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, not like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.10,0:45:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you wanna know\Nwhy I didn't want you to see this?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.19,0:45:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something I wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.61,0:45:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,when our Jupiter was crashing\Nand I didn't think we were gonna make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.71,0:45:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.21,0:45:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.48,0:46:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.35,0:46:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, uh, a testimony.\NIn case anyone found our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.06,0:46:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you find this message, do not weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.44,0:46:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lived a life, I was not a creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.28,0:46:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not like books, but loved my guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.07,0:46:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Brought my music to space\Nand traveled afar."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.21,0:46:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-This is terrible.\N-[both laugh]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.50,0:46:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You try and rhyme\Nwhen you're hurtling to your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.50,0:46:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-Okay. [clears throat]\N-[chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.79,0:46:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"I am Vijay Dhar, aged 16 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.47,0:46:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved free climbing\Nand I faced my fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.68,0:46:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I once had vertigo, but then overcame it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.64,0:47:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Won a state-wide certificate\Nand my mom made me frame it."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.69,0:47:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles] It's from the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.44,0:47:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have never been in love,\Nno girl broke this heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.32,0:47:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems my life is over\Nbefore it could start.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.08,0:47:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you find this message,\Nplease do not weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.70,0:47:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just a particle of space dust\Nyou don't have to keep."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.79,0:47:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna do the whole\N"miles to go before I sleep" thing, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.26,0:47:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.53,0:47:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me which direction\Nthe Robinsons' Jupiter is from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.82,0:47:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,North. About half a mile.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.95,0:47:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.54,0:48:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-You're walking?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.12,0:48:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have something to protect yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.67,0:48:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.59,0:48:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[engines whirring]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.27,0:48:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[engines revving]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.36,0:48:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How's your foot? Getting tired yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.20,0:48:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Not tired enough to keep me\Nfrom kicking your ass when this is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.45,0:48:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don] Can't we just skip this?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.74,0:48:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to the part\Nwhere we're friends again?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.91,0:48:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,West, I don't know how much longer\Nthese are going to hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.33,0:48:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Go inside and tell Aiko\Nwe need to disconnect now,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.63,0:48:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,while we still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.67,0:48:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, aye, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.50,0:48:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.80,0:48:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.13,0:48:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,West, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.38,0:48:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.26,0:48:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.10,0:49:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how much more I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.14,0:49:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Engine's running high.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.56,0:49:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold on, okay?\NDon's pulling everyone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.57,0:49:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Don] You guys almost done? We gotta go.\N-Tapping out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.53,0:49:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-You get it all?\N-[Aiko] Every drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.86,0:49:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool. See you topside.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.53,0:49:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[Aiko] Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.16,0:49:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.33,0:49:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[electricity crackling]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.79,0:49:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-[rumbling]\N-Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.00,0:49:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,-[groaning]\N-[electricity crackling]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.48,0:49:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[engines whirring]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.44,0:49:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-[rumbles]\N-[grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.53,0:49:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.16,0:50:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.08,0:50:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.76,0:50:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don grunting]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.09,0:50:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.36,0:50:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.28,0:50:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. Come on.\NLet's go. Go, go. [grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.28,0:50:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ship creaking]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.75,0:50:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're losing the Jupiter.\NPrepare to detach.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.21,0:50:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,-We need to do it simultaneously.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.71,0:50:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy, you won't believe what I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.88,0:50:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don? Where are you?\N-[Don over radio] On my way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.63,0:50:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[Judy] Don, we can't hold it any longer.\NHurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.05,0:51:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Detach on three. One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.68,0:51:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.60,0:51:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...three! Detach!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.57,0:51:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.90,0:51:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.74,0:51:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[breathing heavily]
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.33,0:51:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Judy grunting]\N-[Victor] Detach!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.25,0:51:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-Judy, what the hell are you doing?\N-Robinson!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.25,0:51:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,West is inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.17,0:51:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don, I can't hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.42,0:51:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-You need to detach now, Judy!\N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.50,0:51:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll do it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.59,0:51:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don, no--
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.19,0:51:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.61,0:52:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[crashing]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.16,0:52:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.95,0:52:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[stutters] He detached it on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.92,0:52:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[continues panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.04,0:52:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He sacrificed for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.51,0:52:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[grunts] Are you crazy?\NI don't even like you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.01,0:52:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,West?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.93,0:52:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[both panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.31,0:52:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.64,0:52:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[all panting]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.98,0:52:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I knew she was too much\Nof a goody-goody to do it herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.19,0:52:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, I was tired\Nof getting yelled at and blamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.65,0:52:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna have to be responsible\Nfor the Chariot going over, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.83,0:52:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.83,0:52:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[stammering] But you were... How did...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.29,0:52:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause I'm a badass, princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.67,0:52:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckling] You're a badass princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.96,0:53:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-What? [stammers]\N-[all chuckle]
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.38,0:53:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. There's a comma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.38,0:53:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-You know, "I'm a badass, comma, prince--"\N-[Judy] Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.14,0:53:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, whatever you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.56,0:53:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, oh, you're welcome, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.60,0:53:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.34,0:53:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um... Hi, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.17,0:53:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.59,0:53:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hanging out.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.97,0:53:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Penny...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.14,0:53:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He seems nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.69,0:54:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.61,0:54:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[Judy over radio] Mom, do you read? \NCan you hear me? Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.07,0:54:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Judy, hi. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.03,0:54:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[Judy] We got it, Mom. We got the fuel.\NAll of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.95,0:54:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.29,0:54:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom? [chuckles] Mom? Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.58,0:54:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. I'm... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.29,0:54:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm good. I'm wonderful, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.80,0:54:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Victor thinks it's too late\Nto trek home,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.80,0:54:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're gonna spend the night.\NI just wanted to let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.34,0:54:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Just get back safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.01,0:54:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles] I will. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.02,0:54:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, too, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.69,0:54:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy... great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.57,0:54:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[Judy chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.61,0:54:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Mom. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.66,0:54:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, hey. How's everything back here?\N-[Maureen sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.20,0:54:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.33,0:54:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.46,0:55:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Four, four, four.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.84,0:55:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Five, five, five. Five. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.93,0:55:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what you're trying to do is,\Nyou're trying to make pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.31,0:55:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to ask the other players\Nif they have any of the cards you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.98,0:55:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously? Do you ever play fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.57,0:55:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so sorry\Nthat I have excellent peripheral vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.28,0:55:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Smith, should we deal you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.78,0:55:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles softly] No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.08,0:55:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] You got an eight?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.25,0:55:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will] Do you have--
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.17,0:55:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[Smith] Uh, Will.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.47,0:55:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask your mom to join?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.68,0:55:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She's busy.\NSaid she had to do some calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.85,0:55:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[Smith] The fuel doesn't get here\Ntill tomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.89,0:56:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And when does she ever have the time\Nto just sit and play with you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.53,0:56:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will] Okay, I'll go ask her.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.66,0:56:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't worry. He'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.79,0:56:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen him make that face before.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.67,0:56:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,-It looks like he's smiling.\N-[chuckles softly]
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.52,0:56:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Angela. What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.61,0:56:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go talk outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.54,0:57:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[Angela] I have no quarrel with you,\NMr. Robinson.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.66,0:57:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing what you think is best\Nto protect your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.67,0:57:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy to discuss this with you,\Nafter my daughter has left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.71,0:57:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.92,0:57:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[John] Angela...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.30,0:57:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,put the weapon down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.72,0:57:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.02,0:57:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To put the weapon down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.65,0:57:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Robot, leave the Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.28,0:57:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will] Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.41,0:57:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all playing Go Fish.\NYou wanna come?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.16,0:57:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, honey, I'd love to but I've got to...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.75,0:57:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? I'd love to.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.62,0:57:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Great, I'll deal ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.25,0:57:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[gunshots]
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.09,0:58:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[echoes] Will! Will, don't go in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.06,0:58:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Will!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.93,0:58:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[gunshot]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.86,0:58:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasps]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.78,0:58:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[gunshots]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.34,0:58:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.47,0:58:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[shuddering]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.56,0:58:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[monitor beeping]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.53,0:59:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A very hard head\Nis one of your dad's finest qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.87,0:59:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.79,0:59:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Judy will check in on him\Nwhen she gets back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.33,0:59:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He just needs some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.94,0:59:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.82,0:59:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.20,0:59:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[Don] I don't know who she is,\Nbut she's not Dr. Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.25,0:59:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I had even more proof in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.38,1:00:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Photographs, diplomas.\NPictures of the man with his family.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.09,1:00:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wearing the St. Christopher necklace.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.47,1:00:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-So why would she--\N-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.89,1:00:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But one thing's for damn sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.10,1:00:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't go through this much trouble\Nunless you have something to hide.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.44,1:00:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Angela.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.94,1:00:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No one will blame you for what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.53,1:00:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all gonna work out fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.17,1:00:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[groans]
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.38,1:00:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.59,1:00:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[sighs] What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.56,1:00:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Everything's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.73,1:00:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Will?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.26,1:01:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the best friend I ever had.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.39,1:01:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.91,1:01:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[Will sniffles]
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.66,1:01:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to be responsible for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.71,1:02:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[cries] Step forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.19,1:02:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasps]
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.99,1:03:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[slow instrumental music playing]